                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">O’Brien</persName>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d197fn1">Repeated to Peking, Paris, Berlin, and St.
                        Petersburg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 14, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Knox instructs Mr. O’Brien to take an early opportunity of communicating
                    formally to the foreign office the substance of the memorandum to the British
                    foreign office which was embodied in the department’s telegram of November 6,
                    taking care to set forth fully the ideas therein contained. Says that the
                    Government of Great Britain has signified its approval of the general principle
                    involved, and directs that he endeavor to secure a like favorable consideration
                    of the project by the Government to which he is accredited.</p>
            </div>
